column5: Simon (Limey Angler) refers to pike as "Yak Fish" and "Lawyers"
Pike: Slough shark

in my group of fishing buddies we call small pike that we throw back johnys cause a guy we know keeps everything he catches. little walleye peckerheads lol a big pike a big old tuna! big bass a fat pig
I agree with Lew. There's musky and then there is bait or dinner. Mind you though, a big pike is fun to tussle with.

I've got a baby muskie in a little fish bowl on my desk at work.  He's really cute, and pretty smart, too.  I even taught him to eat cheezies right out of my hand.  I caught it up north and brought it home to keep my pet snakehead company.  So far they've been getting along great, although all of my guppies seem to have disappeared, and now they just swim around staring at each other.  They're getting a bit big for the bowl, so I'm thinking I might have to flush them soon.  Do you think that's okay?
The Emoticon below was added for this very reason
Post your full address and we'll send someone over to assist you with this....

No need, I came into work this morning and now the snakehead is gone.  It's weird.  My little muskie seems to be getting a bit fat.  I think he could probably use some exercise, so I'm going to take him for a walk on my lunch break.  He shouldn't be out of the water for more than 20-30 minutes, tops.  Hey, which way should I pick him up when I lift him out of his bowl?  I've been doing it by the anal fin, but he doesn't seem to like that very much...

Rock bass = Herb MacRae...  Apparently way back in the day when dad took this guy fishing... He would always catch rock bass while targeting walleye... Like 2-3 a trip... I get like 10 a year...lol  Always called em that since I was a little kid...

If you wanna catch rock bass, fish Paudash Lake. You'll catch 10 an hour easily. They have (or at least used to) a rockbass tournament every year for kids just to get rid of some of them, people will come in with bags full of them. I remember talking to a kid I knew at one of the tournies years ago and he caught over 30lbs of just rock bass that day, and he didn't win lol.

Our family moved to the country when I was 3, my oldest brother was 11 and he was a city kid back then. He caught a tiny catfish while we were fishing and he thought it was a mutated bass. We still tease him about that one lol.

Off the top of my head I can think of these ones but out of curiosity what are others you've heard?   Largemouth:  largie bucketmouth emeraldback   Smallmouth:  smallie bronzeback   Pike:  snot rocket hammer handle northern pikey   Walleye:  wally walter ol' glass eye
